{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ground cardamom, rose petals and sugar in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place rice in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>1 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with sugar and set aside.","Place ghee in mixing bowl and whip <nobr>20 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add flour, salt and reserved ground sugar and rice then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Tip out onto a work surface, wrap in cling film and refrigerate for 45 minutes to firm up. Meanwhile, line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside.","Preheat oven to 150°C. Roll out rested dough on a floured surface until 5 mm thick. Cut out biscuits using a biscuit cutter (approx. 9 cm x 4 cm), and place on prepared baking tray. Re-roll any trimmings until all dough is used.","Bake for 25-35 minutes (150°C) until cooked through and lightly golden. Transfer to a wire rack to cool and harden. Enjoy straight away or store in an airtight container for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["½ tsp ground cardamom","2 tsp dried rose petals","55 g golden caster sugar","40 g long grain rice","100 g ghee","150 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","1 pinch fine sea salt","2 Tbsp water"]}],"id":"r109735","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-SPz5eS1rueA\/XZWeRw9PfBI\/AAAAAAAAexw\/JV9rkK7UZnkfREBnWfUjLmwnNuhB9XtvwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_X-SAquG5TwkeVMKZ.png","title":"Cardamom and Rose Shortbread","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.3 g","fat":"8.5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"15.5 g","calories":"600 kJ \/ 144 kcal"},"usefulItems":"biscuit cutter (approx. 9 cm x 4 cm), cling film, baking tray and paper, rolling pin, wire rack, airtight container, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["We’ve taken a classic British biscuit here and delicately flavoured it with some quintessentially Indian flavours. Lovely served with masala chai or coffee at the end of a meal."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","12 pieces"]}